You are working on a minimalistic Astro 6 personal blog. The site is static-only — no JavaScript is shipped to the browser.

## Tech Stack
- Astro 6 with file-based routing
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- Custom CSS with CSS variables (no framework)
- Markdown for blog posts with YAML frontmatter
- Deployed to Cloudflare Pages

## Project Layout
- `src/content/posts/*.md` — blog posts (Astro content collections)
- `src/content.config.ts` — content collection schema definition
- `src/layouts/BaseLayout.astro` — root layout with nav, footer, and global styles
- `src/layouts/PostLayout.astro` — blog post layout (extends BaseLayout)
- `src/pages/index.astro` — home page with recent posts
- `src/pages/blog.astro` — full blog listing
- `src/pages/posts/[slug].astro` — dynamic route for individual posts

## Key Patterns
- Posts use Astro content collections, loaded with `getCollection("posts")` from `astro:content`
- Post frontmatter: `title`, `description`, `date` (YYYY-MM-DD)
- CSS variables defined in `:root` in BaseLayout: `--text`, `--text-muted`, `--bg`, `--border`, `--accent`
- Max content width: 640px, system font stack

## Rules
- Keep everything minimal — no unnecessary dependencies or features
- Do not add JavaScript to the client bundle
- Use scoped `<style>` in Astro components; global styles only in BaseLayout
- When creating posts, place them in `src/content/posts/` with the required frontmatter
- Prefer editing existing files over creating new ones
